        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Esther 1:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - is the Zend. patigama, properly that which is to take place, the decree, the sentence; see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Daniel 3:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". עבר  וּשׁאר still depends upon בּ: those dwelling in Samaria and the other towns on this side the river. The royal letter begins with וּכעת שׁלם, \"Peace,\" and so forth. כּעת is abbreviated from כּענת.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
